subsection.par:
The initial values for the coefficients must be set properly according to our estimation of the user’s initial trust level. We can link it to domains of users’ email. For example accounts that use a recognized institutional domain (like 


@unimib.it

) will start with a trust coefficient higher that account that are registered with a student domain (like 


@campus.unimib.it

). That methods can be used to distinguish teachers from students and from common users. The initial value of $\alpha $ could also vary over time, studying periodically the overall reliability of the users associated with every domain.
